      <title>Re: Rules regarding macroing</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=227415#M227415</link>
      <description>I believe all programable keyboards/game controllers require you to load their drivers/control programs/etc to work.  Therefore they do have 3rd party macroing software.  The macros for these devices are stored in the driver/control program, not loaded into some memory on the device (that would increase the price).  The device control keys are simply used to trigger key sequences/pauses stored in the control program.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I remember seeing circle straff macros along with automatic weapon change (quake),  for those nsf game controllers, so I would think it would be possible to make a circle kite macro with them or even a triangle kite.  You could have it repeat any sequence of keys, with variable delays, but ofcourse it wouldnt react in any way to game conditions.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I'm curious what exactly you are seeing that seems macroish.  You can accomplish a lot legitimately with the builtin EQ tools.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
